This is the example of deploy simple node js app

1. Install and config git.
2. Install and config aws cli.
3. Install npm.
4. Config SMTP.
5. Add AWS private key in Credentials block - SSH Username "ubuntu" with private key.
6. Add Jenkins item using pipline file. 
6.1. Modify KEY_PAIR value - your key pair name in AWS.
6.2. Modify MAIL_TO value - your email.
6.3. Add creds from the previous point as parameter named "USER_KEY" to the Build.

* if you have EC2 instance in Terminated state, U should delete its Tag named "unique_id"
